<h1>dkim_getdomain()</h1>
<p align="right"><a href="index.html">[back to index]</a></p>

<table border="0" cellspacing=4 cellpadding=4>
<!---------- Synopsis ----------->
<tr><th valign="top" align=left width=150>SYNOPSIS</th><td>
<pre>
#include &lt;dkim.h&gt;

const unsigned char * dkim_getdomain(
	<a href="dkim.html"><tt>DKIM</tt></a> *dkim
);
</pre>
Retrieve either the signer's or author domain associated with a message.
</td></tr>

<!----------- Description ---------->
<tr><th valign="top" align=left>DESCRIPTION</th><td>
<table border="1" cellspacing=1 cellpadding=4>
<tr align="left" valign=top>
<th width="80">Called When</th>
<td><tt>dkim_getdomain()</tt> can be called at any time after a handle
    is initialized with a call to 
    <a href="dkim_sign.html"><tt>dkim_sign()</tt></a> or
    <a href="dkim_verify.html"><tt>dkim_verify()</tt></a>. </td>
</tr>
</table>

<!----------- Arguments ---------->
<tr><th valign="top" align=left>ARGUMENTS</th><td>
    <table border="1" cellspacing=0>
    <tr bgcolor="#dddddd"><th>Argument</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr valign="top"><td>dkim</td>
	<td>Message-specific handle, returned by
        <a href="dkim_sign.html"><tt>dkim_sign()</tt></a> or
        <a href="dkim_verify.html"><tt>dkim_verify()</tt></a>.
	</td></tr>
    </table>
</td></tr>

<!----------- Return Values ---------->
<tr><th valign="top" align=left>RETURN VALUES</th><td>
    <table border="1" cellspacing=0>
    <tr bgcolor="#dddddd"><th>Value</th><th>Description</th></tr>
@MANAGE_AUTHOR_IDENTIFIERS_DOCIF@
    <tr valign="top"><td><tt>any</tt></td>
	<td>The signer's domain for this signing handle.
	</td></tr>
    <tr valign="top"><td><tt>NULL</tt></td>
	<td>The author domain has not been or could not be determined
	    from the message represented by this verifying handle.
	</td></tr>
    <tr valign="top"><td>otherwise</td>
	<td>A pointer to the author domain for this verifying handle.
	</td></tr>
@MANAGE_AUTHOR_IDENTIFIERS_DOCELSE@
    <tr valign="top"><td>any</td>
	<td>The argument for the <tt>domain</tt> parameter to the
	    <a href="dkim_sign.html"><tt>dkim_sign()</tt></a> or
	    <a href="dkim_verify.html"><tt>dkim_verify()</tt></a>
	    call that created the <tt>DKIM</tt> object
	    pointed to by <tt>dkim</tt>.
	</td></tr>
@MANAGE_AUTHOR_IDENTIFIERS_DOCENDIF@
    </table>
</td></tr>

<!----------- Notes ---------->
<tr>
<th valign="top" align=left>NOTES</th> 
<td>
<ul>
<li>
@MANAGE_AUTHOR_IDENTIFIERS_DOCIF@
     This domain is selected by finding the first "From" header field.
@MANAGE_AUTHOR_IDENTIFIERS_DOCENDIF@
     Note that it is
     not guaranteed that
@MANAGE_AUTHOR_IDENTIFIERS_DOCIF@
     this field
@MANAGE_AUTHOR_IDENTIFIERS_DOCELSE@
     the first "From" header field
@MANAGE_AUTHOR_IDENTIFIERS_DOCENDIF@
     was included in the set of fields fed
     to the DKIM signature hashes (assuming it was signed), and in any case
     its value may or may not have been valid at the time the message
     was generated.
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</table>

